{"key":"post-7322558","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7322558</id>\n<content>You should be able to see sclerotia forming by looking through the glass.  A large stone also typically forms on the very top of the grains.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The jar you opened needs to be dumped out into a plate, and then sort through it looking for stones.  Whenever you disturb the grains, they 'look' uncolonized, but if the outside was fully colonized, chances are the inside was too unless you used very large jars where the center became anaerobic.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7330083</next>\n<prev>7322551</prev>\n<first>7322380</first>\n<last>7330083</last>\n<when>1187823993</when>\n<utime>08/23/07 02:06 AM</utime>\n</post>"}